      "content": "Hey, I'm working on this embedded C++ project for an automotive ECU and I'm hitting a wall. The system has a limited heap, and it's slowly running out of RAM over a few hours of operation. I think there's a leak somewhere in the sensor data processing loop.\n\nCan you look at this snippet and give me a systematic way to track down where the memory is actually disappearing?\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data(SensorPacket* packet) {\n    char* log_buffer = new char[256];\n    snprintf(log_buffer, 256, \"Processing packet ID: %d\", packet->id);\n    \n    // some logic here...\n    \n    if (packet->status == ERROR_STATE) {\n        handle_error(packet); \n        // i might be missing something here?\n    }\n\n    update_system_state(packet);\n    delete[] log_buffer;\n}\n```\n\nHow should I approach finding the leak in a real-time environment where I can't just run Valgrind easily?",
      "source": "evaluator"
